So let's draw some
axes over here.

00:00:47.110 --> 00:00:49.490
Let's draw an f-axis.

00:00:49.490 --> 00:00:51.430
That's the number of
fives that I have.

00:00:51.430 --> 00:00:53.310
And let's draw a t-axis.

00:00:53.310 --> 00:00:55.720
That is the number
of tens I have.

00:00:55.720 --> 00:01:00.680
And let's say that this
right over here is 500 tens.

00:01:00.680 --> 00:01:03.350
That is 1,000 tens.

00:01:03.350 --> 00:01:06.480
And let's say this is-- oh,
sorry, that's 500 fives.

00:01:06.480 --> 00:01:08.270
That's 1,000 fives.

00:01:08.270 --> 00:01:14.790
This is 500 tens, And
this is 1,000 tens.

00:01:14.790 --> 00:01:17.860
So let's think about all of
the combinations of f's and t's

00:01:17.860 --> 00:01:20.790
that satisfy this
first equation.

00:01:20.790 --> 00:01:24.050
If we have no tens, then
we're going to have 900 fives.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:31.100
So that looks like
it's right about there.

00:01:31.100 --> 00:01:37.049
So that's the point
0 tens, 900 fives.

00:01:37.049 --> 00:01:38.340
But what if went the other way?

00:01:38.340 --> 00:01:41.770
If we have no fives, we're
going to have 900 tens.

00:01:41.770 --> 00:01:46.230
So that's going to be the
point 900 tens, 0 fives.

00:01:46.230 --> 00:01:50.310
So all the combinations of
f's and t's that satisfy this

00:01:50.310 --> 00:01:54.830
